narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Know more from communicating with professors. It's useful
Interesting topic and thoughts about immunology.

Generally a good introduction into what the professors are doing. The only thing I would recommend is for the professors to make some sort of statement along the lines of this is what I am known for doing in the past and I will/will not continue along this topic in addition to the topic I am presenting. I say this because generally they presented on one topic that they work on and could be working on other things that are not as directly related leading to a misconception about what students think that professor really does.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: It's pretty useful to communicate with professors in a relax environment. Maybe different places for dinners can be considered.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Strongly recommend. It's a good chance to get ideas from professors.
